A "semi-private" API exists for applications that want to avoid the XCB top-half and work directly with the bottom half. The file "xcbxlib.h" contains the interface specification. It is an extremely small interface.

[[toc levels="6"]]

<a name="XCBGetRequestSent"></a>

## XCBGetRequestSent

(xcb\_xlib.c)

`unsigned int XCBGetRequestSent(XCBConnection *c)`

Returns the XCB sequence number of the last request sent on the given connection.

<dl>
  <dt>c</dt>
  <dd>an XCB connection</dd>
  <dt>Returns</dt>
  <dd>a sequence number.</dd>
</dl>

<a name="XCBGetIOLock"></a>

## XCBGetIOLock

(xcb\_xlib.c)

`pthread_mutex_t *XCBGetIOLock(XCBConnection *c)`

Returns the address of the mutex serving as the XCB IO lock on the given connection.

<dl>
  <dt>c</dt>
  <dd>an XCB connection</dd>
  <dt>Returns</dt>
  <dd>a mutex.</dd>
</dl>
